There's no existing project in the directory. I'll create a minimal example showing exactly how to wire this up. Here's the approach using .NET 8+'s built-in `IExceptionHandler`:

**1. Create `Middleware/ApiExceptionHandler.cs`:**

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Diagnostics;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;

namespace YourApp.Middleware;

internal sealed class ApiExceptionHandler(ILogger<ApiExceptionHandler> logger)
    : IExceptionHandler
{
    public async ValueTask<bool> TryHandleAsync(
        HttpContext httpContext,
        Exception exception,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        var (statusCode, title) = exception switch
        {
            KeyNotFoundException => (StatusCodes.Status404NotFound, "Not Found"),
            ArgumentException   => (StatusCodes.Status400BadRequest, "Bad Request"),
            InvalidOperationException => (StatusCodes.Status409Conflict, "Conflict"),
            _ => (0, (string?)null)
        };

        if (statusCode == 0)
            return false; // fall through to default 500 handler

        logger.LogWarning(exception, "Handled API exception: {Title}", title);

        httpContext.Response.StatusCode = statusCode;
        await httpContext.Response.WriteAsJsonAsync(new ProblemDetails
        {
            Status = statusCode,
            Title = title,
            Detail = title,  // safe message — don't use exception.Message
            Instance = httpContext.Request.Path
        }, cancellationToken);

        return true;
    }
}
```

**2. Register in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
// Add these services
builder.Services.AddExceptionHandler<ApiExceptionHandler>();
builder.Services.AddProblemDetails();

var app = builder.Build();

// Add this middleware (before MapGet/MapPost etc.)
app.UseExceptionHandler();
app.UseStatusCodePages();
```

**How it works:**

| Exception | Status | Title |
|---|---|---|
| `KeyNotFoundException` | 404 | Not Found |
| `ArgumentException` | 400 | Bad Request |
| `InvalidOperationException` | 409 | Conflict |
| Anything else | 500 | (generic, no leak) |

- `AddProblemDetails()` ensures the default handler returns RFC 7807 for unhandled exceptions (the `_ => (0, null)` case), with no sensitive details in production.
- `UseStatusCodePages()` converts bare status codes (e.g., from authorization) into Problem Details too.
- Your endpoints just throw — no try-catch needed:

```csharp
app.MapGet("/api/products/{id}", (int id) =>
{
    // This automatically becomes a 404 Problem Details response
    throw new KeyNotFoundException();
});
```

**Example 500 response** (unhandled exception — no internals exposed):

```json
{
  "type": "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc9110#section-15.6.1",
  "title": "An error occurred while processing your request.",
  "status": 500
}
```
